It said the vaccines would cost over $57 million. This will be covered with financial assistance from global vaccine alliance GAVI, which co-runs the COVAX scheme to secure fair access to COVID-19 vaccines for developing countries. It did not specify which vaccines it planned to buy. Mali like other countries in Sub-Saharan Africa is battling a second wave of coronavirus infections, although its infection rate has decreased from a peak in early January, data compiled by Reuters shows.

The West African nation has so far recorded 7 911 cases and 320 deaths.
--Reuters--